HEADWORD: Convenance
<hw>Con"ve*nance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fitness,
suitableness.]</ety> <def>That which is suitable, agreeable, or
convenient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And they missed⟦br⟧
Their wonted <qex>convenance</qex>, cheerly hid the loss.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Convene</ent>⟦br⟧
